As for the geological connection, working off the premise that -B is a God or God-adjacent, I decided to play up the idea of an underworld God by having him specifically rise up from the ground, with the disturbances heralding his arrival. The integration with the ground  made the subterranean connection literal.

As for what exactly is going on in-universe well, that's not something I necessarily care to work out if I have strong imagery to work with.








